<doc>
  <member name="D3D11_FEATURE_DATA_DOUBLES">
    <summary>
      <para>Describes double data type support in the current graphics driver.</para>
    </summary>
    <remarks>
      <para>If the runtime sets <b>DoublePrecisionFloatShaderOps</b> to  <b>TRUE</b>, the hardware and driver support the following <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/d3d11-graphics-reference-sm5">Shader Model 5</a> instructions:</para>
      <list type="bullet">
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dadd---sm5---asm-">dadd</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dmax--sm5---asm-">dmax</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dmin--sm5---asm-">dmin</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dmul--sm5---asm-">dmul</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/deq--sm5---asm-">deq</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dge--sm5---asm-">dge</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dlt--sm5---asm-">dlt</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dne--sm5---asm-">dne</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dmov--sm5---asm-">dmov</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dmovc--sm5---asm-">dmovc</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dtof--sm5---asm-">dtof</a>
          </description>
        </item>
        <item>
          <description>
            <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/ftod--sm5---asm-">ftod</a>
          </description>
        </item>
      </list>
      <b>Note</b>  If <b>DoublePrecisionFloatShaderOps</b> is <b>TRUE</b>, the hardware and driver do not necessarily support double-precision division.
</remarks>
    <seealso href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3d11/d3d11-graphics-reference-d3d11-core-structures">Core Structures</seealso>
  </member>
  <member name="D3D11_FEATURE_DATA_DOUBLES.DoublePrecisionFloatShaderOps">
    <summary>
      <para>Type: <b><a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/WinProg/windows-data-types">BOOL</a></b></para>
      <para>Specifies whether <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dx-graphics-hlsl-scalar">double</a> types are allowed. If <b>TRUE</b>, <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dx-graphics-hlsl-scalar">double</a> types are allowed; otherwise <b>FALSE</b>. The runtime must set <b>DoublePrecisionFloatShaderOps</b> to  <b>TRUE</b> in order for you to use any <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dx-graphics-hlsl">HLSL</a> shader that is compiled with a <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com//windows/desktop/direct3dhlsl/dx-graphics-hlsl-scalar">double</a> type.</para>
    </summary>
  </member>
</doc>